snippet.textDisplay:
I am not Punjabi or never lived in Punjab. Always read about the partition while in school but could never feel what it would be like. I don't understand much of Punjabi but after listening to this song I can only imagine how painful it would have been to be one among those got separated due to partition. My good wishes to all those people, hopefully these borders disappear some day.
Respect for Sir Gurdas Maan!

snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Punjabis,

I always talk to older people who migrated from Pakistan during 1947, they always remember Pakistan and share their experiences with me. I have written a few lines to express their feelings.


OOS PAAR - ACROSS THE BARBED WIRES 

Khichi thi kisine lakeeren kabhi gusse mein, Jo bankr aaj diwar khari hai,
zikar oos paar ka lahoo le aata hai ankhon mein masoom naye patton (leaves) ke
Kucsh ankhon mein yadon ka dariya aaj bhi behta hai,
Oos paar dil aaj bhi dharkta hai un drakhton (trees) me jab bachpan ke khel zhalak ate hain pal bhar ke liye
Kabhi reh jati hain adhoori woh sanse sapno se, jab purane ghar se khulti hain aankhen anjaan mitti mein,
Chahe mulkh do hain, par roohen pahoonch jaati hai sapno mein kabhi oos paar
Nafrat ke lapte ho jitni bhi oonchi, dilon ki khwahishon ko jala nahin patti,
Galiyon ki, melon (fairs) ki, kuon (wells) ki, bachpan ki baaten zikar karti hai jaren (roots) hameshan naye patton (leaves) se oos paar ki
Rooh aaj bhi karti hai doston se milne ki jo rehten hai oos paar,
Uttar jaana chahte hain oos dariya me jo behta hai oos paar
kaat denaa chahte hain wo lohe ki taron ko, jo khichi thi kissine gusse mein,
mann trafta hai har waqt kyon ki rokti hain wo diwaren hamen jane se oos paar
